{"title":"Manitou Mattoc Pro Limited Edition","link":"https://theradavist.com/manitou-mattoc-pro-limited-edition/","date":1710510453000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"5329\" height=\"3553\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/527066-Mattoc-LTD-WHT-3190-RETOUCHED-b213d1-original-1708537236.jpg?fit=1200,3553&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/527066-Mattoc-LTD-WHT-3190-RETOUCHED-b213d1-original-1708537236.jpg?w=5329&amp;quality=75 5329w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/527066-Mattoc-LTD-WHT-3190-RETOUCHED-b213d1-original-1708537236.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/527066-Mattoc-LTD-WHT-3190-RETOUCHED-b213d1-original-1708537236.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/527066-Mattoc-LTD-WHT-3190-RETOUCHED-b213d1-original-1708537236.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/527066-Mattoc-LTD-WHT-3190-RETOUCHED-b213d1-original-1708537236.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/527066-Mattoc-LTD-WHT-3190-RETOUCHED-b213d1-original-1708537236.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Manitou was the original mountain bike suspension option for 90s hardtails and to commemorate its legacy, the brand brought back its OG logos and styling on one of the best looking forks we’ve seen: <a href=\"https://hayesbicycle.com/products/mattoc-pro-limited-edition\" target=\"_blank\">Mattoc Pro Limited Edition</a> ($1,099.99). Let’s check it out.<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"8171\" height=\"5448\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Manitou-Mattoc-LTD-WHT.jpg?fit=1200,4800&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Manitou-Mattoc-LTD-WHT.jpg?w=8171&amp;quality=75 8171w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Manitou-Mattoc-LTD-WHT.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Manitou-Mattoc-LTD-WHT.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Manitou-Mattoc-LTD-WHT.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Manitou-Mattoc-LTD-WHT.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Manitou-Mattoc-LTD-WHT.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>The original Manitou fork was versatile by necessity when, regardless of your discipline, there was one choice for your suspension needs. The new Manitou Mattoc Pro Limited Edition borrows its iconic look from 1992 yet takes all the technology from 2024 and packs it in a 34mm stanchion 29” wheel package that spans multiple riding disciplines.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Johnny-O-Maras-Yeti-ARC-14.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Johnny-O-Maras-Yeti-ARC-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Johnny-O-Maras-Yeti-ARC-14.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Johnny-O-Maras-Yeti-ARC-14.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Johnny-O-Maras-Yeti-ARC-14.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Tomac-Raleigh_05.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Tomac-Raleigh_05.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Tomac-Raleigh_05.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Tomac-Raleigh_05.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Tomac-Raleigh_05.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Juli-Furtado-Yeti-C-26-38.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Juli-Furtado-Yeti-C-26-38.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Juli-Furtado-Yeti-C-26-38.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Juli-Furtado-Yeti-C-26-38.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/Juli-Furtado-Yeti-C-26-38.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Out of the box, the Mattoc Pro LE is configured to 140mm travel. With the travel spacers included in the box, along with the easy-to-follow service instructions found on <a href=\"https://hayesbicycle.com/products/mattoc-pro-limited-edition\" target=\"_blank\">Manitoumtb.com</a>, the travel can be internally adjusted from 110-150mm.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529486-MattocPro2022-5669-3f62a0-original-1709924125.jpg?fit=1200,3000&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529486-MattocPro2022-5669-3f62a0-original-1709924125.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529486-MattocPro2022-5669-3f62a0-original-1709924125.jpg?resize=1200,1800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529486-MattocPro2022-5669-3f62a0-original-1709924125.jpg?resize=768,1152&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529486-MattocPro2022-5669-3f62a0-original-1709924125.jpg?resize=1024,1536&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529486-MattocPro2022-5669-3f62a0-original-1709924125.jpg?resize=1365,2048&amp;quality=75 1365w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1333\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529487-MattocPro2022-knob-d53850-original-1709924369.jpg?fit=1200,2000&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529487-MattocPro2022-knob-d53850-original-1709924369.jpg?w=1333&amp;quality=75 1333w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529487-MattocPro2022-knob-d53850-original-1709924369.jpg?resize=1200,1800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529487-MattocPro2022-knob-d53850-original-1709924369.jpg?resize=768,1152&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/03/529487-MattocPro2022-knob-d53850-original-1709924369.jpg?resize=1024,1536&amp;quality=75 1024w\" /></p>\n<p>Weighing in at 1750g, a 59g savings over its predecessor, the lightweight 34mm chassis owes its stiffness to key Manitou technologies, most notably the reverse arch. The polished crown is heavily machined both internally and externally, removing any excess weight while optimizing the chassis stiffness.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wheel Size: 29″</li>\n<li>Weight: 1750g</li>\n<li>Offset: 44OS</li>\n<li>Ride Height: 140mm = 552 a2c</li>\n<li>Spring: Dorado Air with Infinite Rate Tune (IRT)</li>\n<li>Compression Damping: Sealed Cartridge TPC+ with Hydraulic Bottom Out (HBO)</li>\n<li>Rebound Damping: Sealed Damper TPC</li>\n<li>Adjustments: Air, IRT, Rebound, HS, and LS Compression</li>\n<li>Steerer: 1.5″ Tapered</li>\n<li>Crown: Forged Aluminum, Hollow Bore</li>\n<li>Leg Diameter: 34mm</li>\n<li>Leg Material: 7000 Series Butted Wall Aluminum</li>\n<li>Brake: Post Mount 160mm</li>\n<li>Axle: 15mm x 110mm Hexlock</li>\n<li>Max Tire Size: 67mm</li>\n<li>Options: Fender Kit, TSR, Hexlock SL2</li>\n<li>E-Bike Compatible: Yes</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://hayesbicycle.com/products/mattoc-pro-limited-edition\" target=\"_blank\">Manitou.</a></p>\n<p>Don’t miss our Vintage Bicycles posts with Manitou forks below!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/manitou-mattoc-pro-limited-edition/\">Manitou Mattoc Pro Limited Edition</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"c8bcc9bc4a57b8ecc8c2c8ed0ca56e162e5ad0a81f175bb98935ae88f723729f","category":"Cycling"}